body:
by **alexander.orlov@loxal.net**:

<pre>In template.html files you can embed CSS and JavaScript. Both languages are using curly
brackets.

CSS example: 

strong {
 color: red;
}

JavaScript example: 

function test() {
//
}

To be able to use CSS and JavaScript within a template.html file you have to override
the default settings, which might happen quite often as you'll often use embedded
CSS/JavaScript within template.html â€” even just temporary to test something. So you
have to use the the SetDelimis func all the time to override the default.

Django's (Python) templating engine uses &quot;{{&quot; / &quot;}}&quot; as default
delimis. 

My proposal is to use the same delimis as Django's templating engine.

I could provide a patch to fix this issue if you're willing to accept it.</pre>
